A Maryland environmentalist alarmed by the decline ofthe Chesapeake Bay's native oyster population is trying to get it onthe federal Endangered Species list -- sparking an uproar of oppositionin the oyster industry from Maine to Louisiana.
"Oysters in the Chesapeake Bay are in serious, serious trouble.They've had such a drastic decline in the past century," said JamieKing, an oyster specialist in the NOAA's Chesapeake Bay office.
The Chesapeake Bay watershed covers 64,000 square miles andincludes parts of six states.
Red tide algae can cause paralytic shellfish poisoning.
